A Damsel is a NPC you're friends with who is very good at accidentally getting caught by enemy plots and contrivances as a justification for you to be involved without contradicting your character's backstory. They should be well liked enough that you want to save them over and over again.

Forms:  
Base Form \- Your civilian attire, almost no Sidereal powers, can be hurt.  
Magical Form \- Your normal Magical Girl Form, can't be physically hurt.  
Crisis Form \- Your emergency button, nearby civilians cannot be hurt, but you take their damage when it ends.

Combat details:  
Each round when its your turn you can:  
In the fight

* Move one distance closer or further to   
* Use one action (changing stance is an action)

Out of the fight

* Roll a d4 to see how far you can move  
* If you move to a location with a threat (like a minion) you spend the rest of your turn dealing with it and cannot move further 

Poise  
To win  
Get yours to 10	Or	Get enemy's to 0   
To lose  
Get yours to 0		Or	Get enemy's to 10

Stances:  
Wild: automatically move closer to foe and gain 1 poise at the end of the round  
Ballanced: automatically avoid movement effects, can't gain or lose more than 1 poise per round  
Preparing: lose one poise at the end of the round and increase your Prep count by one for the purposes of actions 

Diagram for how to be knocked stanceless:  
Wild beats Prep  
Prep beats Ballance  
Balance beats Wild

How to transform:  
Requires one of the following:

* Catchcry  
* Henshin pose  
* Transformation tool

Causes one of the following:

* Sound and lights  
* Explosion behind you  
* Nudity

If someone sees you transform your identity could be exposed, take precautions.
